HEADWORD: Alpha paper
<hw>Al"pha pa"per</hw>. <fld>(Photog.)</fld> <def>A sensitized paper for
obtaining positives by artificial light. It is coated with gelatin
containing silver bromide and chloride.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

